%YAML 1.1
%TAG !u! tag:unity3d.com,2011:
--- !u!114 &11400000
MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: a4a2d85a031f79d48bc826866dadb256, type: 3}
  m_Name: ListOfPages
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::BookPages
  pages:
  - pageHeading: STORY
    pageWriting: "(In case you forget, the spirit has a fondness for erasing your
      memories) You\u2019re a mystic from a long line of carnival fortune tellers,
      your ancestors struck a deal with a soul hungry spirit, in return you get the
      power to read fortunes and make wishes come true, the spirit is linked to your
      bloodline forever and gets the chance to steal your customers souls with their
      own interpretation, they will try and read the cards negatively in order to
      kill them, if he succeeds he claims their soul. You are a 10th generation fortune
      teller and the main attraction of the carnival, known as the Trans Balkan Express.
      Due to another deal your ancestors made with the \u201COutrageously Wonderful
      Mr. Zagoo\u201D if you ever run out of customers you will burst into flames."
    pageImage: {fileID: 0}
  - pageHeading: 'FORTUNE READING RESOLUTION '
    pageWriting: "Every fortune reading is a struggle between your silver tongue
      and the Spirit lurking behind the cards. At the end of a session, both sides
      gain Favor based on the cards drawn and the words spoken during the reading.
      Whoever holds the greater Favor claims victory over the customer\u2019s fate."
    pageImage: {fileID: 0}
  - pageHeading: 'GAINING FAVOR '
    pageWriting: "Your Magic Meter is one of the strongest sources of power during
      a reading. As it fills, it can provide up to +50 Favor. Reaching the maximum
      instantly secures victory. Good Cards strengthen your reading and each one
      grants +10 Favor. Neutral cards do not provide Favor on their own, but they
      can still contribute to other effects. The audience also reacts to the overall
      energy of the card spread through a mechanic known as Crowd Energy. If the
      draw contains more Good cards than Bad cards, you gain +15 Favor from the crowd\u2019s
      approval. If there are more Bad cards than Good cards, those +15 points are
      instead awarded to the Spirit. Neutral cards are ignored for this comparison,
      and ties provide no bonus to either side. A special bonus called Hopeful Silence
      can occur if every drawn card is Neutral. If this happens and your reading
      contains at least two different Hope Words, you gain an additional +4 Favor.
      However, the presence of any Good or Bad card immediately cancels this effect.
      Your reading can also gain strength through Theme Echoes. Each card has its
      own theme word list, and using words connected to that theme empowers the reading.
      For every card in order from 1 \u2192 2 \u2192 3, you can gain Favor depending
      on how many matching theme words are spoken. Using one matching word grants
      +3 Favor, two matching words grant +5, and three or more matching words grant
      +8. Across all three cards, the maximum possible gain is +24 Favor. Finally,
      the overall emotional tone of your reading affects the customer\u2019s belief
      in your fortune. Hopeful, comforting, or inspiring language increases your
      Favor, while cruel or overly harsh wording weakens it. Depending on the balance
      of your wording, the tone system can grant anywhere between 0 and +20 Favor. "
    pageImage: {fileID: 0}
  - pageHeading: 
    pageWriting: "A special bonus called Hopeful Silence can occur if every drawn
      card is Neutral. If this happens and your reading contains at least two different
      Hope Words, you gain an additional +4 Favor. However, the presence of any Good
      or Bad card immediately cancels this effect. Your reading can also gain strength
      through Theme Echoes. Each card has its own theme word list, and using words
      connected to that theme empowers the reading. For every card in order from
      1 \u2192 2 \u2192 3, you can gain Favor depending on how many matching theme
      words are spoken. Using one matching word grants +3 Favor, two matching words
      grant +5, and three or more matching words grant +8. Across all three cards,
      the maximum possible gain is +24 Favor. Finally, the overall emotional tone
      of your reading affects the customer\u2019s belief in your fortune. Hopeful,
      comforting, or inspiring language increases your Favor, while cruel or overly
      harsh wording weakens it. Depending on the balance of your wording, the tone
      system can grant anywhere between 0 and +20 Favor. "
    pageImage: {fileID: 0}
  - pageHeading: "THE SPIRIT\u2019S FAVOR "
    pageWriting: 'The Spirit gains power through darkness and misfortune. Every Bad
      Card drawn grants the Spirit +10 Favor, while Neutral cards provide nothing.
      The Spirit also benefits from its own version of Theme Echoes and Tone Matching.
      Unlike your readings, however, the Spirit grows stronger from words tied to
      fear, despair, misery, and cruelty. Soft or hopeful language weakens the curse,
      while dreadful and threatening wording empowers it further. '
    pageImage: {fileID: 0}
  - pageHeading: 'CARD MORALS '
    pageWriting: 'Every card in the deck carries a hidden moral alignment that influences
      the balance of Favor during a reading. Understanding the nature of each card
      is essential if you hope to outwit the Spirit. Good Cards grant +10 Favor to
      you whenever they appear in the spread. These cards represent fortunate omens,
      hopeful futures, and uplifting energies. Bad Cards instead empower the Spirit,
      granting it +10 Favor for each one drawn. These cards feed fear, despair, and
      corruption into the reading. Neutral Cards do not directly grant Favor to either
      side. However, they can still activate special effects such as Hopeful Silence
      and influence systems like Crowd Energy depending on the overall draw. '
    pageImage: {fileID: 0}
  - pageHeading: 'THEME VOCABULARY '
    pageWriting: "Each card belongs to a mystical theme. During the reading, words
      connected to that card\u2019s theme can trigger powerful Theme Echo bonuses.
      Theme matching is checked from left to right across the spread, meaning Card
      1 uses its own theme list, Card 2 uses its own list, and so on. The Greed theme
      contains words tied to excess, wealth, and endless appetite. Words such as
      greed, hunger, feast, glutton, gold, coin, wealth, covet, and banquet all resonate
      with Greed-aligned cards. The Vanity theme revolves around pride, appearance,
      and self-image. Words like mirror, pride, ego, beauty, reflection, mask, and
      vain contribute toward Vanity echoes. The Chaos theme embraces destruction
      and instability. Terms such as storm, disorder, spiral, mayhem, wreck, shatter,
      and wild strengthen Chaos cards. The Power theme represents authority, domination,
      and burden. Words including control, throne, crown, rule, dominion, command,
      reign, and burden all resonate with Power-aligned cards. Efficient readings
      usually aim for around two matching words per card, as additional matches provide
      diminishing rewards. Only words belonging to the active card\u2019s theme count
      toward that card\u2019s score. For example, using Vanity words on a Chaos card
      grants no bonus at all. "
    pageImage: {fileID: 0}
  - pageHeading: 'TONE OF THE READING '
    pageWriting: "The emotional language used during a fortune is just as important
      as the cards themselves. Both you and the Spirit gain Favor based on the overall
      tone of your words. Your readings gain power from Hope Words and lose strength
      from Harsh Words. The system calculates your Tone score by heavily rewarding
      hopeful language while penalizing cruel or fearful wording. Final Tone Favor
      is always limited to a range between 0 and 20. The Spirit follows the opposite
      rule. Harsh, dreadful, and threatening language strengthens its curse, while
      hopeful wording weakens it. Its Tone score is also capped between 0 and 20.
      Words only count once per reading, regardless of how many times they are repeated.
      Capital letters are ignored, and special phrases such as \u201Cwalk lightly\u201D
      or \u201Chunger for\u201D only count if written exactly as shown. Hopeful language
      includes words tied to healing, guidance, growth, and comfort. Examples include
      hope, peace, heal, blessing, courage, balance, support, warmth, forgive, and
      renew. Harsh language includes words associated with suffering and decay. Examples
      include ruin, doom, curse, rot, dread, hollow, death, darkness, shatter, and
      corruption. A skilled fortune teller learns to lean heavily into hopeful language
      while avoiding harsh phrasing whenever possible \u2014 even when describing
      dark or dangerous themes. "
    pageImage: {fileID: 0}
  - pageHeading: 'THE MAGIC METER '
    pageWriting: "Every fortune teller\u2019s tent is powered by a mystical Magic
      Meter. Some tents use a short dial while others use a much longer one, but
      the rule is always the same: reaching FULL means absolute dominance over the
      reading. As the meter fills, it grants increasing amounts of Favor, scaling
      up to a maximum of +50 Favor before completion. However, the moment the meter
      reaches FULL, the duel ends instantly in your favor. The Spirit\u2019s curse
      is silenced completely, regardless of its score or wording. A wise teller keeps
      one eye on the cards\u2026 and the other on the meter. "
    pageImage: {fileID: 0}
  - pageHeading: 'QUICK START GUIDE '
    pageWriting: "Before submitting a fortune, quickly examine the flow of the reading.
      First, check the morals of the drawn cards. A spread filled with Good Cards
      gives you natural momentum, while too many Bad Cards strengthen the Spirit.
      If every card is Neutral, then the outcome depends almost entirely on your
      wording, making Hope Words especially important for securing the Hopeful Silence
      bonus. Next, glance at the Magic Meter. If it has reached FULL, the reading
      is already won and no further strategy is needed. After that, focus on building
      Theme Echoes. Try to match words to each card\u2019s theme in the exact order
      the cards were drawn. Consistent theme matching is one of the strongest ways
      to build Favor quickly. Finally, control the emotional tone of your reading.
      Fill your fortune with hopeful, comforting language while avoiding harsh or
      dreadful wording. Winning the tone battle often decides close matches against
      the Spirit. "
    pageImage: {fileID: 0}
  - pageHeading: 'FAVOR REFERENCE '
    pageWriting: 'In a standard three-card duel, Favor can be earned from several
      different sources throughout the reading. The Magic Meter can provide up to
      +50 Favor, unless it reaches FULL, in which case it grants an immediate victory
      instead. Good Cards can provide up to +30 Favor for you across the spread,
      while Bad Cards can grant up to +30 Favor to the Spirit. The Crowd Energy bonus
      can award +15 Favor to either side depending on whether Good or Bad cards dominate
      the draw. The special Hopeful Silence bonus grants an additional +4 Favor if
      every card is Neutral and enough Hope Words are used. Through careful word
      choice, Theme Echoes can contribute up to +24 Favor for either side. Finally,
      the emotional Tone system can grant as much as +20 Favor depending on how hopeful
      or dreadful the reading becomes. No matter how the numbers are calculated,
      remember one final rule above all others: If the Magic Meter reaches FULL,
      the fortune teller always wins. '
    pageImage: {fileID: 0}
